Hi Ben,

Sure it's https://www.safensound.net.au/wp-admin

The theme was loading the 'Alt' text of the images, this was the white text that was appearing. I believe they only started appearing as there was previously no Alt text entered for those particular images. The Alt text should not be displayed. It's actually there for visually impaired website visitors and used by audio page readers to describe the images to those that can't see them. But it is a tiny ranking factor, so it's good to have it there as best practice (not seen though). I hope that helps?

Hi Heath,
